\sphinxAtStartPar

\section{Export Tool (on home page)}
\label{\detokenize{Third Party/data-export-tool:export-tool-on-home-page}}

\end{itemize}


\section{Daily task (cron job)}
\label{\detokenize{Third Party/data-export-tool:daily-task-cron-job}}\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
Daily task cron job execute \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{C:\textbackslash{}MIS\textbackslash{}Task Scheduler\textbackslash{}MIS Daily Task.exe}} for dashboard data and pivot data. This cron job run by windows task scheduler every day.

\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
Git repository: \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{https://gitlab.com/mis\sphinxhyphen{}projects/mis\sphinxhyphen{}task\sphinxhyphen{}scheduler.git}}

\end{itemize}


\section{Monthly task (cron job)}
\label{\detokenize{Third Party/data-export-tool:monthly-task-cron-job}}\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
Monthly task cron job execute \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{C:\textbackslash{}MIS\textbackslash{}Task Scheduler\textbackslash{}MIS Monthly Task.exe}} for log HF and VMW. This cron job run by windows task scheduler every month.

\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
Git repository: \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{https://gitlab.com/mis\sphinxhyphen{}projects/mis\sphinxhyphen{}task\sphinxhyphen{}scheduler.git}}

\end{itemize}


\section{DB Backup (cron job)}
\label{\detokenize{Third Party/data-export-tool:db-backup-cron-job}}\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
DB Backup task cron job execute \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{C:\textbackslash{}MIS\textbackslash{}Task Scheduler\textbackslash{}MIS DB Backup.exe}} for dashboard data. This cron job run by windows task scheduler every day.

\item {} 
\sphinxAtStartPar
Git repository: \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{https://gitlab.com/mis\sphinxhyphen{}projects/mis\sphinxhyphen{}db\sphinxhyphen{}backup.git}}

\end{itemize}

\section{Place}

\subsection{Check place is modify}
\label{\detokenize{api/v4:check-place-is-modify}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{api/v4:get--api4-Places-isModify}}\pysigline{\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{GET~}}\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{/api4/Places/isModify}}}
\sphinxAtStartPar
To check if place is modified in system.

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{note}{Note:}
\sphinxAtStartPar
if return empty it mean nothing change.

\sphinxAtStartPar
if return any json data it mean place has been changed. and the json data that return is new data of place.
\end{sphinxadmonition}
